Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.41,0:00:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So what we haven't mentioned so far, we said,\Ntruth only comes, meaning only comes out of context.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.26,0:00:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And one context that we haven't spoken about this morning, of course, is karma.\NThat you have both discernible context, undiscernible context,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.42,0:00:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and non-identifiable context called karma.\NThat's why much scientific experimentation doesn't make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.18,0:00:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And so they come up with contradictory results because they don't define the context.\NThe reason computers can never create an artificial intelligence,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.52,0:01:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it can only do logic trees, logic trees in human intelligence.\NHuman intelligence is a subjective evaluation
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.79,0:01:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of an infinite number of millions of data of information\Nwhich it intuitively wins its way through without actually processing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.45,0:01:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason you can't...\NYou can't do a computer replica of human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.76,0:01:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is for one thing, the major portion of the context is missing.\NIt can only program content.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.04,0:01:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,One piece of context that is not available to put on the computer\Nbecause it's unknown, is karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.04,0:01:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what you say.\NAnd that which is in the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.81,0:01:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So all you could put on the computer would be that which is reasonably logically recallable.\NIt totally, you cannot put what's in the unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.76,0:01:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because by definition it's unconscious.\NIf it's unconscious, it is not available data.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.07,0:02:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't put that in the computer.\NContext is non-linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.93,0:02:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Computers only deal with the linear.\NTherefore, meaning, significance, value,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.50,0:02:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't put Mother's Day on a computer\Nbecause the reverence,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.16,0:02:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you put reverence into a computer?\NLogic series, you can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.88,0:02:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause it's a feeling state, it's a way of being with,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.96,0:02:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a way of being with the totality of that which you are\Nand the totality of the feminine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.61,0:02:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The way this consciousness is with the feminine\Nevolved over eons.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.02,0:02:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Evolved over eons.\NIt's reverence for the feminine is eons old.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.97,0:02:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThat cannot be put into a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.96,0:03:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's context that gives the thing meaning and value,\Nsignificance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.02,0:03:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Our spiritual work then derives its power,\Nderives its power.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.16,0:03:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We said you can go to metaphysical lectures\Nfor 35 years and never change one iota.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.97,0:03:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the person has denied the power within them.\NThere's the power to transform the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.25,0:03:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of the word,\Ninto the world of the word.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.62,0:03:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Into the subjective experiential world of spiritual truth.\NThe power is within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.87,0:03:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does the power come from?\NThe power comes from willingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.91,0:04:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Willingness about what?\NThere was the willingness to accept that women were to be revered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.72,0:04:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandparents said that, my father said it.\NThere was no resistance to that, no resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.77,0:04:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth instantly at home.\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.06,0:04:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no trust.\NThere was trust in the words.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.45,0:04:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There was trust in the sincerity with which they were said.\NThere was trust in the integrity of the speaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.00,0:04:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo out of love for the source of the information,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.31,0:04:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,all resistance was relinquished.\NAnd that was accepted as truth and incorporated within for a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.30,0:04:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Same thing should then ideally happen with spiritual work.\NThe power of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.57,0:04:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of self.\NThe consciousness of the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.63,0:05:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The educator should be sufficient that one's trust in it is profound like it was in my\Ngrandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.98,0:05:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the resistance dissolves itself.\NIf I tell you that the feminine is infinitely divine, worshipful as the expression of God
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.12,0:05:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in that expression, you know that's the truth, is it not?\NIs that the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.88,0:05:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NYou reverence that within yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.88,0:05:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The feminine within yourself you reverence as the expression of God, as it expresses\Nitself in the feminine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.91,0:06:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As it comes out of form, the divine begins to take on attributes which we eventually\Nrecognize as form.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.91,0:06:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference between male and female, divinity has already come into form as male and female,\Nbecause tomorrow is Mother's Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.31,0:06:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm concentrating on the feminine, the magnificence and the beauty of divinity as expressed as\Nthe feminine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.87,0:06:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So our acceptance of that doesn't depend on its being accepted by other people.\NIt makes no difference to me how other people hold women within their psyche.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.19,0:06:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's their problem.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.23,0:06:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no problem.\NThere's no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.23,0:06:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no problem.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.36,0:06:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no conflict and no problem with the way it is within.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.51,0:06:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As close to its being, as close to its divine nature as possible.\NSo what did the grandparents do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.22,0:07:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My uncle, my, all the men in the family held women who reverenced it.\NWhy was it so powerful?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.56,0:07:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It was because they were holding it as close to its divine origination as possible.\NThey were holding it as a condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.81,0:07:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Not as your uncle, I mean, not as your aunt or your grandmother or your mother, as personages,\Nbut they were holding it as a powerful field of realization.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.23,0:07:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got it.\NI got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.23,0:07:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I got what it was.\NI got what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.74,0:07:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The divinity innate within the feminine, that's what I got.\NThat's why it is worthy of reverence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.94,0:07:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?\NSo our resistance to incorporating truth and resistance,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.42,0:08:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to incorporating truth and instantly recognizing it then,\Nthe resistance to it can be bypassed by faith, love, the trust and openness,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.26,0:08:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and the divinity that we intuit as the field out of which the information is coming.\NIt is out of infinite love that that is forthcoming from consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.23,0:08:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness into the awareness of the listener.\NIt doesn't take 35 years of attending lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.40,0:08:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes one instant of trust.\NOne instant of trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.16,0:08:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,One reason we use kinesiology is to clear the obstacles to trust.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.28,0:09:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If I tell you that the expression of motherhood,\Nand this calibrates at 540,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.99,0:09:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and the way women are held by political positions,\Nand the way women are held within the urbic world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.22,0:09:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if we calibrate those levels,\Nthat sort of removes the doubtfulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.46,0:09:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the doubtingness of the intellect.\NThe intellect is the great doubter,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.72,0:09:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and the great blocker to truth.\NSo we try to also handle the ego at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.15,0:09:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So all that I've ever spoken of became an absolute reality in one instant,\N35 years ago or whatever it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.62,0:09:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Somewhere in the long distant past.\NAll that I'm saying today became an instant reality, wordlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.88,0:10:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what speaks right now.\NWhat speaks right now searches for how to express that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.00,0:10:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to bypass the resistance of the intellect, the mind, and the ego.\NAnd you see, as I saw as a boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.00,0:10:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the incredible,\Nmagnificent sense of the divinity of woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.50,0:10:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,One instant, my grandfather said,\Nyou'll never speak to your grandmother that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.96,0:10:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I got how she was held.\NSo it takes one instant to get what you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.82,0:10:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Not 35 years.\NIt only takes one instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.29,0:10:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In one instant, the ego lets go its resistance\Nout of faith, confidence, and trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.38,0:10:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it does.\NWhen my father said that to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.48,0:11:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it was not a lie.\NI knew it was truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.66,0:11:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So all resistance stopped.\NAnd that became incorporated into the truth of my own reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.14,0:11:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth of my own reality.\NSo I'm going to use personal experience to demonstrate a certain principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.62,0:11:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The last thing I want to happen is people come to these lectures\Nand then tell me nothing has changed and nothing's happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.07,0:11:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll kill myself.\NIn a dead body, I killed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.22,0:11:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I went to all these lectures and nothing changed.\NI will.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.57,0:11:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to die and it's going to be on your head.\NYou made me do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.57,0:11:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the you made me do it game, right?\NAh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.91,0:12:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.\NSo you might say,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.01,0:12:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in a certain context then,\Nthat I belong to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.46,0:12:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything I'm saying today belongs to you.\NIs that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.40,0:12:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NEverybody here totally owns what's being said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.24,0:12:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here totally owns the speaker.\NSo what is the speaker then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.00,0:12:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The speaker is what?\NSpiritual educator.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.00,0:12:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.\NHow's that for a term?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.28,0:12:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a good term?\NYou like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.28,0:12:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSpiritual educator.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.37,0:12:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,\Nwe share with you the truth that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.73,0:12:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it was subjectively experienced\Nand as it is present within.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.13,0:12:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NBut that's not comprehensible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.84,0:12:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So we go back to what it is that\Nkeeps it from being comprehensible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.84,0:12:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to explain it in terms that are\Nunderstandable to the scientifically trained mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.05,0:13:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to pay attention.\NJesus wasn't dealing with scientifically trained people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.25,0:13:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NThey couldn't read or write for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.79,0:13:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a snap of a job.\NThey hadn't read all the books.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.62,0:13:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There weren't any books on the whole thing.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.67,0:13:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NThings have evolved in the last couple thousand years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.32,0:13:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And the listener, the student of today,\Nis somewhat different.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.32,0:13:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Considerably different.\NFar more sophisticated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.08,0:13:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 400s.\NThose people there that Jesus dealt with
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.13,0:13:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,were probably in the 200s.\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.13,0:13:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.10,0:13:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we ask that?\NWe have permission to ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.60,0:13:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That became followers were below 200\Nto start with.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.65,0:14:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo it was the power of the truth coming through
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.72,0:14:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that transformed the people\Nand the people instantly saw
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.62,0:14:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth that he revealed.\NThat was his authority
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.00,0:14:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which they became enlightened.\NThe saints were all became enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.00,0:14:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result of the capacity\Nto drop all resistance
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.51,0:14:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and just respond to that truth.\NJust as I did with my grandparents
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.54,0:14:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and my father\Nabout who women really were.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.79,0:14:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got in an instant\Nwho they really were.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.62,0:14:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't need to read any books on the subject.\NJust got it right off the bat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.94,0:15:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One instant I got who women were.\NAnd in the lectures all we want
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.92,0:15:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is in one instant\Nwe get who we really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.92,0:15:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us here are a gift to the world.\NLet's see if we're a gift to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.57,0:15:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is a gift to the world.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.98,0:15:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo our being here at this moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.98,0:15:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us who are here at this moment\Nare collectively a gift to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.98,0:15:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The world calibrates at 207.\NThis group calibrates at 430
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.47,0:15:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,as they walked in the door.\NThat's already a gift to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.87,0:15:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of just who we are.\NWho you are is a gift to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.33,0:15:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Different way to hold yourself.\NWhen you walk through Walmarts
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.74,0:15:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and you smile at somebody,\Nthey get it as a gift to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.79,0:16:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice how they light up?\NYou ever walk through Walmarts and smile at people?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.09,0:16:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody lights up all the way down the aisle.\NJust try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.91,0:16:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean you probably never noticed it.\NShe's pushing this and you're pushing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.95,0:16:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You look over and smile at her.\NIt knocks them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.95,0:16:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,She's so happy that somebody smiles at her\Nand recognizes her
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.95,0:16:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that she just beams right back to you.\NIt's like instant love all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.95,0:16:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to do that in the streets of New York City.\NThe streets of New York City are like Walmarts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.65,0:16:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I lived in New York City.\NI would just walk down the street
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.65,0:16:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and just love everybody as they came along.\NPeople just beamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.65,0:16:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You can stop anybody on the street of New York\Nand start talking about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.54,0:16:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell do you think about me or so and so?\NThey'll instantly give you a talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.54,0:16:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you've known each other for 30 years.\NThere's no barrier there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.54,0:16:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I love the streets of the city of New York.\NYou can stop anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.67,0:17:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's a character.\NIt's terrific.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.67,0:17:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The dialect, the whole style,\Nwhat it means to be a New Yorker,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.68,0:17:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the certain implicit understanding\Nof the rights and wrongs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.31,0:17:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Under certain circumstances, stealing is not really stealing.\NHe left it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.31,0:17:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He left it out.\NOh, well, if he left it out, that's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.60,0:17:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Totally different.\NChange of context.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.60,0:17:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He left it laying there.\NWell, okay, he left it laying there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.96,0:17:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Even a judge wouldn't convict you, probably.\NHe left it laying there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.15,0:17:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He left it laying there.\NA whole different context of ethics and morality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.98,0:17:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is acceptable there\Nis not acceptable here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.98,0:17:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The context of New York City\Nis different than the context of elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.88,0:17:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand that?\NThe context makes it different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.91,0:18:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The context makes its meaning\Nand its significance become different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.20,0:18:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So context defines meaning and significance.\NTo do the same thing here
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.20,0:18:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be nothing at all in New York\Nwould be ethically a different animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.20,0:18:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A different animal altogether.\NHe just can't take his change
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.97,0:18:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and not feel guilty about it.\NWell, he left all his change on the bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.97,0:18:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NHe went to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.97,0:18:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you expect?\NIt's going to be there when you get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.90,0:18:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the great block?\NWhat is the great block to keep it from sinking in?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.90,0:18:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NHave you got any idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.81,0:18:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We tried to approach it from the viewpoint\Nthat the ego as a totality
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.81,0:18:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,will not tolerate\Nany infringement of its boundaries
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.95,0:19:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,because it realizes that it's a threat to its totality.\NIt's an interlocking system
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.95,0:19:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and to let in love\Nmeans that the end is inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.55,0:19:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's so.\NTo allow in love
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.42,0:19:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,means to the ego ultimate dissolution.\NAha!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.77,0:19:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Above all else then,\Nego fears love.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.13,0:19:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego is scared to death of Mother's Day.\NThe ego is scared to death
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.95,0:19:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of what Mother's Day really is.\NIt's scared to death
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.20,0:19:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of what Mother's Day really is,\Nreally is, really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.20,0:19:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The recognition of the divinity of love\Nin its expression,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.51,0:19:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of course on Mother's Day as the feminine,\Nwould mean that love
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.19,0:19:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as a prevailing dominant value\Nwould infiltrate all of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.48,0:20:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And that would be the end\Nof many corporations
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.73,0:20:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and political positions and all.\NTherefore, yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.24,0:20:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego is scared to death of Mother's Day.\NI don't know if it's scared of Father's Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.24,0:20:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll wait till June.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.26,0:20:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So love then becomes the greatest threat\Nto the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.26,0:20:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to not go to 35 years of lectures\Nis nothing happening then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.64,0:20:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The secret of it is love.\NThe secret is love for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.99,0:20:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The secret of it is\Nfaith and confidence
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.05,0:20:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and the integrity of the source of the truth.\NAnd one means of accomplishing that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.70,0:20:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is by kinesiologic testing.\NTo what degree you can trust
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.70,0:21:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the validity of what is being said.\NIt comes through the energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.21,0:21:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated energy field of the speaker.\NThe level of the truth then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.21,0:21:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth because truth is only meaningful\Nwithin a certain context.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And what is the context of the words\Nthat have been said?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.24,0:21:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We could test the truth\Nof Deutschland über alles.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.96,0:21:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we could test the context\Nout of which it came,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.05,0:21:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness of Adolf Hitler.\NActually, Adolf Hitler played upon
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.33,0:21:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of fascism in Germany\Narose out of a philosophic position.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.53,0:21:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A professor...\NIt's in my book, I forget his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.07,0:21:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Pfaffenhofer or something.\NThey justified the German invasion by...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.10,0:21:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a doctrine of\NRäumsleben or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.58,0:21:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Living room.\NLebensraum.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.68,0:22:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That Germany had the right to invade\Nneighboring countries
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.68,0:22:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because it needed room to live.\NBoy, that was a weak one, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.81,0:22:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But it built the whole country.\NThe whole structure came out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.43,0:22:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Room to live.\NGolly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.14,0:22:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I transmit\Nto the fellow drivers on the highway.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.42,0:22:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I need room to drive, folks.\NTherefore, I have the right
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.68,0:22:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to crash my car into his\Nand knock him off the road
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.68,0:22:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because I need driving room.\NThat's a rather weak intellectual position,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.68,0:22:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't it?\NDid we ever calibrate that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.99,0:22:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,No, let's see.\NDeutschland über alles
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.33,0:22:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 100, 110,\N120, 130, 140, 140.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.44,0:22:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAdolf Hitler at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.44,0:23:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to resist.\NCalibrate over 120, 130, 140, 150.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.63,0:23:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It corresponded, huh?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.91,0:23:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo then the demagogue finds
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.91,0:23:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside in human nature\Nand knows how to directly appeal to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.91,0:23:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The smart politician knows\Nwhat the consciousness level of mankind is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.90,0:23:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he can easily summon up that hatred.\NHe knows that hatred is there
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.22,0:23:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,only waiting to be summoned up.\NAt the opposite end,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.24,0:23:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we know in spiritual work,\Nbecause of the reality of existence itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.20,0:23:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that the capacity for love\Nand for enlightenment is also available
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.49,0:23:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,within human mankind.\NSo we'll leave hatred to other people
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.74,0:23:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to summon that forth.\NAnd all we want to recognize here
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.00,0:23:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is that divinity is the source of your own existence.\NIt is out of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.00,0:24:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that consciousness arises.\NIt is consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.57,0:24:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is the field\Nholding us all together,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.57,0:24:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which everybody is able to hear\Nand experience that which is being said.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.05,0:24:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence within all of us\Nis what allows us
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.16,0:24:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience\Nthe subjective experience
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.85,0:24:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which we are\Nand which we're trying to verbalize here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.22,0:24:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So reality then is a radical subjectivity.\NWe'll get to a lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.24,0:24:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,on meditative techniques at all.\NBut at all times,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.61,0:24:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the shortcut to God is\Nto merely realize
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite presence\Nof your own capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.31,0:25:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience\Nand the source
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.14,0:25:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own existence.\NNothing has within it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.39,0:25:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity\Nto create its own existence
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.39,0:25:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,out of what comes existence itself.\NWe bypass causality
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.77,0:25:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,as a plausible explanation.\NAnd I think in the first lecture
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.82,0:25:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we knocked causality on its butt.\NAnd the world hasn't heard of that yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.82,0:25:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but the days of causality\Nare over, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.82,0:25:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's get to it.\NBecause the ego will say,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.99,0:25:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,well, what about causality\Nas an explanation?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.15,0:25:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is created\Nin such a way
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.48,0:25:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that its essence\Nunfolds
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.86,0:25:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,due to the divinity\Nof its source.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.33,0:26:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It is because of the divinity\Nof the source of creation
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.33,0:26:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that all things are perfectly\Nwhat they are at any moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.33,0:26:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That which appears catastrophically awful\Nappears that way
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.88,0:26:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's out of context.\NBecause of who you are
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.25,0:26:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in the present,\Nthat looks terrible
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.65,0:26:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in the past.\NThat's already a judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.65,0:26:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The awful\Nmanifesting its awfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.53,0:26:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is supposed to be awful\Nin the awfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.53,0:26:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of its awfulness.\NAnd it's perfectly awful
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.93,0:26:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in the dreadfulness\Nof its horrific
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.98,0:26:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and horror.\NDespicable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.43,0:26:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's supposed\Nto be that way, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.95,0:26:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So you know what it is.\NNow you know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.95,0:27:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, we choose differently this time.\NWe look at the dead bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.95,0:27:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,on the battlefield,\Nwe look at the run over children,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.18,0:27:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and something within us begins to change.\NBut it changes so slowly, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.26,0:27:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you calibrate yourself,\Nconsciousness level of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.26,0:27:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,century by century by century,\N190, 190 you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.26,0:27:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, didn't mankind learn anything?\NWar of 1812?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.40,0:27:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,One war right after another.\NHitler was really so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.23,0:27:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, he was really stupid.\NNapoleon had just pulled that trick
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.45,0:27:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and blown it.\NAnd he went around and did the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.45,0:27:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Invade Russia.\NEast and west are from the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.53,0:27:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How can anybody be so stupid?\NStupid, stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.15,0:27:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So that ignorance and that stupidity\Nwe're trying to find a way through today.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.15,0:27:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha and Jesus both said,\Nthe only sin is that of ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.40,0:28:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Sin as a moralistic put down\Nis really useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.02,0:28:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's using guilt as a hammer\Nto beat people to death with
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.02,0:28:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or beat yourself to death with.\NIt says there is ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.22,0:28:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignorance seems to be innate then\Nin the structure of the ego itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.90,0:28:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you go to 35 years of lectures\Nand not get anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.90,0:28:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Still be the same person.\NThere's something within
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.95,0:28:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego itself\Nthat accounts for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.07,0:28:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Century after century.\NMillions slaughtered.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.07,0:28:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You go to the next century.\NWould it be better? You'd think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.07,0:28:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No, still 190. Millions more slaughtered.\NStill 190. Millions more slaughtered.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.07,0:28:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, whoa, there's something\Nthat's really thick-headed about the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.81,0:28:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some innate stupidity.\NInnate stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.81,0:29:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There we got it today.\NThe ego is just stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.96,0:29:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is dumb.\NSo we should treat it like an imbecile.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.92,0:29:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Stupid.\NDumb. Pitiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.60,0:29:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We should feel sorry for the ego.\NIt is so dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.96,0:29:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It can sit there for 35 years\Nand not get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.69,0:29:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I think maybe what happened was...\NYeah, I see what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.22,0:29:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah.\NAlright. The source
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.44,0:29:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,from which you are learning\Nor hearing or something
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.52,0:29:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,has to be of a certain dimension.\NTo break through the resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.52,0:29:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I held my grandfathers\Nwith reverence and respect
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.51,0:29:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and my father and my uncle.\NBecause of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.82,0:29:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't argue.\NAnd it was appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.91,0:30:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The way women were treated\Nwas appropriate to the way
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.91,0:30:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that they were held.\NAnd they showed me how they were held.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.32,0:30:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason it rang true\Nis because it was based on spiritual reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.35,0:30:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the feminine is the expression\Nof divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.38,0:30:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In that genre\Nof human expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.48,0:30:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got it in an instant.\NThe same thing should happen
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.81,0:30:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in any spiritual literature,\Nspiritual teaching, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.31,0:30:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The respect, the letting go of resistance\Nto the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.08,0:30:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of its source.\NWhat is the source of its truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.89,0:30:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of its truth\Nis the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.61,0:30:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,within\Nthat speaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.17,0:30:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Classically with speaking now\Nit would be called
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.22,0:31:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in Sanskrit\NPurusha.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.22,0:31:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Purusha would be the essence\Nof the self
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.55,0:31:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of the teacher\Nwhich is expressing itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.55,0:31:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what\Nis expressing itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.55,0:31:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do\Nwith the body
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.94,0:31:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is using at the moment.\NIt will use anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.20,0:31:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't trust Purusha.\NIt will grab anybody, speak to anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.29,0:31:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Get there.\NThe source of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.01,0:31:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the realization\Nof the truth of all spiritual teachings
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.01,0:31:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is the\Nself within you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.66,0:31:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You have within yourself\Nthe power
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.06,0:31:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of recognition.\NIt's only the recognition
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.46,0:31:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,if what my grandparents\Nhad told me, my grandfathers
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.76,0:32:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,my uncle\Nhad told me
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.85,0:32:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,was not innately true.\NIt would not have resonated within.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.46,0:32:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because\Nof the presence of truth within me
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.46,0:32:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I was capable\Nof hearing the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.50,0:32:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It is only because of\Nthe presence of truth within
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.50,0:32:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone here\Nthat there is any capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.50,0:32:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to extract any truth\Nout of the research that we've
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.23,0:32:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,done and we are sharing with you.\NOh my goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.42,0:32:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is consciousness\Na byproduct
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.42,0:32:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of the spirit\Nentering a dense matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.42,0:32:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh boy, oh boy.\NOh boy, oh boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.42,0:32:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NWe've got enough questions
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.01,0:32:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep us busy for a while.\NEach question reflects
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.08,0:33:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what we intend to talk about anyway\Nand it just reminds me
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.08,0:33:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of what we were going to talk about.\NThe disassembly of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.70,0:33:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,takes eons of time.\NMost people in this audience
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.40,0:33:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,have been here 50, 60 times\Nbefore to try to accomplish
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.18,0:33:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that which\Nhappens within an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.18,0:33:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I use the word happens\Nlinguistically to make sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.18,0:33:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To sense\None's reality is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.19,0:33:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only a matter of\Nknowing where to look.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.25,0:33:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look over here, you're looking\Nat the written word.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.96,0:33:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,35 years of the written word.\NWhere is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.75,0:33:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're looking for?\NYou can all sense
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.72,0:34:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,right in this instant.\NRight in this instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.06,0:34:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,These people are already distant.\NI see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.51,0:34:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What you do is\Nyou catch
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.78,0:34:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencing\Nof the world
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.09,0:34:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,just prior to the mind's\Ncommentary about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.21,0:34:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you back off from the mind\Nyou'll find an inner stillness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.94,0:34:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which hasn't said anything yet.\NYou live in the space
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.26,0:34:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,before the world has said anything yet.\NWhen you walk outside
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.82,0:34:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you're struck by the beauty\Nof the surroundings.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.82,0:34:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't said anything about it yet.\NYou live in that space.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.57,0:34:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The space is pre-verbal.\NPrior to mentalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.96,0:35:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with\Nverbalization
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.78,0:35:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is\None has to come out of that space
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.53,0:35:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and come forward into that\Nverbalization because that's what
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.55,0:35:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the world expects.\NYou
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.15,0:35:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,world speak\Nor the world doesn't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.15,0:35:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,because nothing is being spoken.\NRight at this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.09,0:35:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,just sense within yourself\Nthat which hasn't had a second yet
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.23,0:35:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to make any comment about\Nwhat the speaker is saying yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.69,0:35:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind's commentary\Nis a delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.86,0:35:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a split second delay\Nand you live in that experience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.86,0:35:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,before any comment.\NWhen you dive off a diving board
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.53,0:35:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no thinkingness about it\Nas you hit the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.61,0:36:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The thinkingness comes later.\NA split second later
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.61,0:36:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that dive wasn't made correctly.\NOw.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.61,0:36:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That dive wasn't made correctly.\NBut that's a split second
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.61,0:36:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,after you go splat on the water\Nand realize
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.84,0:36:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that full gainer\Nwas only a three-quarter gainer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.94,0:36:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Red Valley Express\Neven as you think
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.96,0:36:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not getting it\Nyou're there right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.40,0:36:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now within everybody's consciousness\Nis
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.50,0:36:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of consciousness itself\Nprior to any kind of content.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.03,0:36:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nyou draw back and you live
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.46,0:36:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in the space\Nright before the mind starts to make commentary.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.61,0:37:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And you hold back\Nin this space
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.86,0:37:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond the mind's thinkingness.\NThinkingness should be
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.82,0:37:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,voluntary.\NI think when I'm forced to think
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.40,0:37:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is forever asking you to think\Nand comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.40,0:37:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No end to it.\NYou're always exhausted
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.34,0:37:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,by coming out of the infinite peace\Nand beauty of silence
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.09,0:37:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because the world has some\Ndumbbell question.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.78,0:37:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?\NWhat is it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.26,0:37:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes energy.\NI have a new
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.59,0:37:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful telephone\Nat home.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.59,0:37:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a space phone\Nor whatever they call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.75,0:37:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand electronics and all that stuff.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.07,0:37:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you've got to read all this fine writing.\NNo matter what you buy
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.32,0:38:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it's got a 16-page manual.\NGet away from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.32,0:38:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,My favorite radio\Nis in the waiting room of my office.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.32,0:38:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the radio I grew up with.\NIt's got a dial.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.32,0:38:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes on, volume, off\Nand on.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.55,0:38:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The world hates\Nthat kind of a radio, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.55,0:38:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NNowadays, somebody gave me an electronic
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.57,0:38:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,radio, a new radio.\NIt's got a 14-page
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.57,0:38:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't even\Nget it to tell time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.57,0:38:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got one. I don't know what\Nyou do to make it even tell time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.61,0:38:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what I'm saying?\NYou get dragged into this complexity.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.61,0:38:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It pulls all your energy and your interest\Nand your survival gets pulled
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.61,0:38:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,out there.\NYeah, Ramana Maharshi said it correctly
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.67,0:38:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,when I read Ramana Maharshi.\NI said, that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.73,0:38:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind gets pulled into the world\Naway from the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.55,0:39:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And one's reality\Nis prior to the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.65,0:39:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,One's reality is\Nprior to the self
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.73,0:39:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as what?\NAs a condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.44,0:39:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As a field.\NSo your reality is a field.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.26,0:39:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the innate field\Nout of which,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.26,0:39:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,just prior to thinking this,\Nwhen you wake up first thing in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.15,0:39:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the field is there.\NYou don't even know who you are yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.42,0:39:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know what your name is.\NYou don't know where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.48,0:39:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,There's just the awareness of awareness itself.\NAnd at that point,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.01,0:39:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,all you know is that you're awake.\NPeriod.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.21,0:39:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that phase when you wake up?\NYou know you're awake and that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.30,0:40:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what the condition is\NIt's always present.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.38,0:40:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When thinking that I am that which is talking\Nand thinking is what's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.38,0:40:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The identification of self,\Nof reality as the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.76,0:40:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when that goes away,\Nin an instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.34,0:40:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,there's deadening silence.\NThen the question is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.86,0:40:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,how to be in the world\Nof dead silence
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.96,0:40:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,when the world is talking all the time.\NIt's hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.67,0:40:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It took many years to adjust.\NHow to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.73,0:40:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people when they go into that space\Ndon't readjust.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.73,0:40:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not reenter the world.\NSome kind of karmic momentum.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.80,0:40:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people do return to the world.\NAlright, so
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.03,0:40:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,at all times you're really making an effort\Nto come out of the state of inner peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.03,0:41:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of like\Nhaving to wake up
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.28,0:41:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and deal with the world.\NLook within yourself and see
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.88,0:41:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,there's really a reluctance\Nto deal with all this thinkingness
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.88,0:41:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and judgmentalism\Nand emotionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.13,0:41:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's exhausting.\NWithin yourself you'll find
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.57,0:41:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,man, I'm really tired.\NIs everybody here tired?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.86,0:41:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, I'm exhausted\Nwith dealing with the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.86,0:41:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why people look forward\Nto dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.17,0:41:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait until it's over.\NIt drags on
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.50,0:41:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and on and on.\NYou know what the end is anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.50,0:41:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's the big deal?\NAn hour later it's all the same, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.84,0:41:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Which brings up the question\Non Alzheimer's.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.21,0:42:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody asked me about Alzheimer's\Nand I've dealt with Alzheimer's
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.34,0:42:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot the last five or ten years.\NIn Alzheimer's
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.57,0:42:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the spirit leaves,\Nstarts leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.80,0:42:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it is.\NYou're not really there anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.00,0:42:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You're like an enlightened person.\NYou ask an enlightened person
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.21,0:42:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,what is today's date?\NWhat the hell does he care what today's date is?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.21,0:42:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't live in today's date.\NThere's no date in reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.21,0:42:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only the experience\Nof nature being what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.21,0:42:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If I go and ask a tree, I say, what's the date?\NIt doesn't live in the world of dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.30,0:42:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The tree doesn't live there.\NThe tragedy of Alzheimer's
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.11,0:42:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the witness of Alzheimer's.\NThe suffering is in the witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.65,0:42:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When you don't know what the hell\Nthe date is anymore, are you suffering?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.59,0:42:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I've asked a thousand Alzheimer's patients,\Nhow are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.01,0:43:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.\NThey say that you can't eat,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.71,0:43:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're this and that.\NOh, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.57,0:43:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what day it is today?\NOh, I don't pay attention to those things anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.69,0:43:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What year were you born?\NOh!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.13,0:43:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they say to me.\NWhat year were you born?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.13,0:43:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!\NLike asking a woman her age,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.13,0:43:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, 40 years ago.\NYou never asked a woman her age.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.13,0:43:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!\NThen they make up stories
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.13,0:43:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to make you happy.\NI mean, you obviously want an answer from them,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.42,0:43:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so they'll make up a story on the spot,\Nand five minutes later,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.42,0:43:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they've forgotten the story.\NDo you fear Alzheimer's?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.23,0:43:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Why?\NBecause people identify
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.11,0:44:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,with the content of ego as self,\Nand there are people
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.36,0:44:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that are frightened to death\Nof losing their memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.30,0:44:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell if you don't remember\N1932 to 1934?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.30,0:44:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so precious\Nthat you want to be able to recall it instantly?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.30,0:44:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Right? Anything?\NA person says,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.61,0:44:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid I might lose my memory.\NI hope. I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.61,0:44:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing better could happen to you.\NMemory is the recall
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.71,0:44:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of perceptual illusion\Nas it compounded over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.96,0:44:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's like the poison well, folks,\Nthough it's killing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.96,0:44:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, do I feel sorry\Nfor the Alzheimer's patient? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.13,0:44:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the witness, the family.\NTwo-year-old granny's losing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.28,0:44:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They're weeping and sobbing.\NIs granny weeping and sobbing? No, she's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.73,0:45:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it here\Nin this nursing home?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.50,0:45:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to all the nursing homes\Nin the Ababai County
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.50,0:45:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,for close to ten years, right?\NEvery day I knocked my brains out.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.50,0:45:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn't any other doctor\Nthat would go see them, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.94,0:45:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The county was happy somebody\Nwould make a house call
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.44,0:45:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and go to the nursing home\Nbecause it was horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.44,0:45:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I loved them all.\NThe men and the women
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.76,0:45:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,were all cute as could be.\NAnd it's because you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.76,0:45:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,what's lovable has been\Ncompletely preserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.09,0:45:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What's lovable is totally there.\NWhat's irrelevant has disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.84,0:45:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All they've lost is what's irrelevant.\NAs you get closer to the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.73,0:45:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,some people have,\Nlet's not even title it anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.42,0:45:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the spirit begins to leave\Nbefore the physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.44,0:45:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people, by the time\Nthey physically die,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.53,0:46:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the spirit's left years ago.\NI knew Bill Wilson.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.15,0:46:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the founder of AA.\NBill would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.15,0:46:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and I actually treated him\Nthe last year of his life,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.15,0:46:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,vitamin E and various stuff,\Nantioxidants we were fooling around with.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.92,0:46:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And he would drift off.\NAnd then
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.21,0:46:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,his watchers would be concerned\Nthat Bill had drifted off.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.21,0:46:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it, Bill?\NI'd say, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.26,0:46:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,there are many places you can go in heaven.\NHe'd been visiting heaven back and forth
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.26,0:46:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,like he was shopping for a future resident.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.26,0:46:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see in old people then,\Ndo I fear Alzheimer's in myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.88,0:46:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NNo, I don't fear Alzheimer's in myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.90,0:46:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm 75.\NI have senior moments, however.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.69,0:46:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I call a lot of people,\Nwhat's his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.90,0:47:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What's his name and what's her name?\NI know who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.90,0:47:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happens then\Nis that which is important
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.53,0:47:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and significant\Nis no longer located
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.53,0:47:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,within the ego's functions.\NIt's not important to be able to figure out,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.03,0:47:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to read this manual\Nand figure out how to push all these buttons
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.03,0:47:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I can set the watering system\Nfor every third day
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.61,0:47:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and half time on rain days\Nand three days on...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.61,0:47:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked at one in the store the other day,\Na new watering system thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.61,0:47:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It was mind-boggling.\NIt has so many bells and whistles
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.61,0:47:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you couldn't figure out how the hell\Nto make it water the lawn, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.15,0:47:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It would serve 12 stations.\NWhy would you... 12 stations?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.15,0:47:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want one that turns it on and off,\Nyou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.19,0:47:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,On at three, off at four.\NDon't you have one like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.19,0:47:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we don't have one like that.\NI'll tell you folks,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.69,0:48:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the easiest way is in the morning\Non the way to work you turn the watering system on
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.69,0:48:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and on the way you turn the hose on,\Nthe sprinklers, and when you come home
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.69,0:48:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you turn it off.\NIs that simple or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.75,0:48:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Just saved you $72.\NOh, you can turn it on and off yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.23,0:48:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Never thought of that.\NAfter breakfast you turn it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.65,0:48:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Before dinner you turn it off.\NThat's all it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.21,0:48:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so reality then\Nis the world of simplicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.50,0:48:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The person with advanced Alzheimer's\Nis ultra simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.59,0:48:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They have no needs, no wants,\Nyou say to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.78,0:48:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,how are things here?\NFine.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.82,0:48:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How are they treating you?\NFine.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.30,0:48:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you rather be someplace else?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.73,0:48:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,While you're still hanging onto the mind\Nin the past, you grieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.78,0:49:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But as happily Alzheimer's progresses,\Nyou lose that attachment to the past
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.78,0:49:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you're not grieving\Nthat you're not living on the farm in Michigan anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.51,0:49:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Except to the witness,\Nhe is probably closest to enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.57,0:49:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,than most human consciousness.\NThat's a statement of fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.67,0:49:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to look at the Alzheimer's patients\Nand I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.57,0:49:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Christ, he's a Buddha.\NWhat's his problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.57,0:49:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem.\NHow are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.76,0:49:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.\NHow are things here yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.80,0:49:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NWhere are you going tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.84,0:49:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They're living in the instant of now\Nin which the self is still present
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.84,0:49:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's only present in the self\Nwith a capital S.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.84,0:49:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not present as a small s.\NAlzheimer's is the dissolution
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.88,0:49:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of the self with a small s\Nand those who are more spiritually advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.09,0:50:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,see that the self with a capital S\Nis still vitally there.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.09,0:50:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just as loving, warm, friendly,\Nresponsive in the instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.38,0:50:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we summon forth in Walmart.\NWhen you lose your
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.38,0:50:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,identification with your persona,\Nyou're just walking with a basket,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.38,0:50:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a nobody.\NThese two nobodies can instantly be
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.38,0:50:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,very friendly and quite loving with each other.\NIsn't that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.90,0:50:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're walking in Walmart\Nand somebody bumped into your basket
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.90,0:50:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly she started to cry,\Nyou'd say to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.90,0:50:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,huh, you know what I mean?\NBecause that veneer that prevents us
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.90,0:50:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,from realizing who we are\Nhas been removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.03,0:50:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Alzheimer's from a certain viewpoint\Nthen is a blessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.42,0:50:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You forget that you're dying\Nso you don't have to even grieve that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.98,0:50:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't have Alzheimer's\Nthen you've got to worry that you're dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.98,0:50:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've got Alzheimer's,\Nit doesn't even enter your mind to worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.21,0:51:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thing is effortless, painless,\Nand I think on the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.57,0:51:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd hardly notice the difference.\NDo you? Could you go on the other side?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.78,0:51:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you notice the difference?\NOh yeah, you notice the body's laying there.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.88,0:51:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who's gone out of body\Nrealizes that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.88,0:51:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize, oh, where's the body?\NIt's laying there in the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.09,0:51:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot.\NI thought I was still that body.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.36,0:51:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So helpers come to remind you\Nthat that isn't yours anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.36,0:51:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need it anymore.\NYou don't want it anymore anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.36,0:51:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a mess.\NYou leave it at 93,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.36,0:51:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,blind, deaf, dumb, crippled,\Nwith arthritis and one leg missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.36,0:51:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, who's going to hang on to it?\NSo that's my view of old age suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.38,0:51:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The suffering is due to\Nhanging on to what?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.53,0:51:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What it was.\NAnd the absolute refusal to surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.53,0:51:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Death and dying Alzheimer's\Nare moments of great opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.78,0:52:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach spiritual enlightenment.\NThey're great moments because
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.59,0:52:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the investment in the world,\Nthe investment in the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.59,0:52:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the functions of the body and the mind\Nhave diminished to the point
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.59,0:52:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's easy to let it go.\NEasy to let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.61,0:52:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,To be in the space just prior to thought.\NSo your reality
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.82,0:52:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is the sense\Nof presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.17,0:52:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Your sense of being here.\NYou hear what he's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.07,0:52:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't necessary to really understand it.\NYou sense that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.09,0:52:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you are present.\NYou sense that you're in the presence
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.44,0:52:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presence of the allness\Nof us here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.88,0:52:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like when you walk out in nature.\NJust before your stupid mind
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.30,0:52:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,says, isn't that a beautiful tree?\NYou catch the space in which you saw
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.30,0:53:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,a tree's beauty without comment.\NThat's the space you live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.01,0:53:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Just prior to thought.\NIt's easy to just
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.19,0:53:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,fall back into it.\NIt's not like something you have to accomplish
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.19,0:53:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,through years of study and meditation.\NThe willingness to trust it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.67,0:53:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and just drop into that,\Nback into that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.80,0:53:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That is your reality.\NYour reality is a priority
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.80,0:53:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to any programming.\NYour reality is
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.46,0:53:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,what is in the computer world\Nthe software and hardware.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.38,0:53:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Your beauty is the hardware\Nwhich is always present.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.30,0:53:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Prior to hitting the button\Nand getting the software.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.30,0:53:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, isn't that a beautiful tree?\NIt's too late already.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.40,0:53:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,However, even while you're saying that\Nyou can back off from the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.40,0:53:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and not identify with that statement.\NThe two things exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.44,0:54:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is both context and content.\NThe two things exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.78,0:54:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,One can realize the foolishness\Nof the statement
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.80,0:54:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and simultaneously\Nbe aware of the beauty of the woods
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.05,0:54:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,prior to any comment.\NWe'll do one or two more questions
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.65,0:54:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we'll break for lunch.\NTrying to read these is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.05,0:54:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They really have\Nvery good handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.92,0:54:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like reading the stuff\Non the back of the clock
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.15,0:54:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,on how to make it work.\NHow should we hold the situation
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.86,0:54:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Middle East\Ncoming back to the present world?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.17,0:54:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The presidency\Ncalibrates around 450
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.17,0:54:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and it has throughout the centuries.\NI think a few of them
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.26,0:54:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in olden times\Nbut in modern times
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.40,0:54:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the average consciousness level\Nis about 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.40,0:55:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Roosevelt was like 499 or something.\NChurchill was 510.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.84,0:55:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness then\Nof the leaders of the modern world
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.67,0:55:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,are usually in the mid-400s.\NThey're going to do
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.67,0:55:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what appeals to reason\Nthe intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.67,0:55:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,intelligence,\Nresearch,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.94,0:55:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,their advisors.\NThey're going to do what
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.00,0:55:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going to pull together\Nthe best advice team
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.00,0:55:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they will give it\Na slight preference
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.00,0:55:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,due to political position.\NCurrent president
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.00,0:55:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,has no problem\Nwith right versus wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.15,0:55:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Right is right and wrong is wrong.\NWhat's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.11,0:55:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Within that context,\Nit's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.11,0:55:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now your question is\Nshould that context apply?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.53,0:56:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When a tiger is about to rip\Nyour jugular vein out,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.53,0:56:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the context is a little different\Nthan looking at a
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.73,0:56:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,tiger in the zoo.\NThe context is a little different.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.73,0:56:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What's permissible?\NThe alternatives
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.40,0:56:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,are somewhat different\Ndepending on context.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.61,0:56:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's the context of the zoo\Nthat makes it a little different
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.61,0:56:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,than the jungle.\NThis has to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.01,0:56:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,My goodness,\Nthese are tough ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.17,0:56:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my golly.\NOh my golly.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.46,0:56:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We got some really brilliant minds\Nhere today.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.98,0:56:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We will answer all these things\Nin one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.46,0:57:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just answer one more question\Nand then we will break for lunch
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.42,0:57:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because these are a lot to sort of\Nlook at and pull out the essence of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.86,0:57:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot what I was\Ngoing to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.00,0:57:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of questions about\Ncalibrations of the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.00,0:57:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrating levels of consciousness\Nis only a tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.00,0:57:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of getting information.\NIt doesn't get you enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.13,0:57:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But it does tell you\Nwhat's a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.26,0:57:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What's a dead end?\NAnd also what's a pitfall?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.44,0:57:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What to avoid?\NWhich way to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.61,0:57:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's helpful\Nin the first direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.73,0:58:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the capacity\Nto tell the truth about anything
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.73,0:58:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,instantly brings up a zillion questions\Nabout everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.01,0:58:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to look at the intention\Nbehind the curiosity,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.01,0:58:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,behind the question.\NVery often you find out more
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.48,0:58:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,about what you wanted to know\Nby examining the reason
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.46,0:58:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,why the question is coming up.\NIt's been a unique opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.82,0:58:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because we've found out\Nthat there is access
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.01,0:58:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that accounts for\Nthe spin of this photon
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.01,0:58:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in this direction.\NInstantly the spin of the photon
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.01,0:58:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in this direction.\NAnd the only thing that changed
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.05,0:58:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,was human consciousness observed it.\NHuman consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.11,0:58:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,did nothing but look at this photon.\NInstantly the photon rotates this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.26,0:58:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This photon rotates this way.\NInstantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.69,0:59:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No connection between the two whatsoever.\NThe only connection that's possible
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.26,0:59:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,would be that there's\Na field, a field,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.30,0:59:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,common, a matrix,\Na matrix, a latticework.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.30,0:59:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's called in quantum mechanics\Nhypothesized
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.30,0:59:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a matrix,\Na matrix, a latticework.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.61,0:59:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that under which\Nthe whole universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.32,0:59:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the reality of matter,\Nthe reality of all that exists
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.32,0:59:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,then arises out of that\Nwhich is invisible,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.32,0:59:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,indefinable, undefinable,\Nunlimited.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.90,0:59:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that sense of that\Nwithin yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.67,0:59:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a matter of sensing it.\NIt's a matter of intuition.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.80,0:59:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You go back within yourself\Nto that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.80,0:59:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,there prior to hearing this word.\NThere is something there
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.34,0:59:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,right before this word\Nis heard and right before
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.34,1:00:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind thinks of a\Nreaction to the word.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.59,1:00:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in that space,\Nthe most likely place
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.55,1:00:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and situation\Nto find that space
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.21,1:00:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that we call enlightenment\Nis while you're eating cookies.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.21,1:00:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Diana's cookies.\NIf that don't take you there,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.26,1:00:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing will.\NSo we'll resume then
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.26,1:00:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in exactly one hour, okay?\NAnd we'll do more questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.26,1:00:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have a chance to look at the questions\Nduring the break.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.76,1:00:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well we were asked to test\Na number of various things.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.86,1:00:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of them I already know the answer\Nbut just for fun, a near death experience
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.11,1:00:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to ask that question.\NI don't think it's
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.34,1:00:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,correctly phrased right.\NNear death experience
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.38,1:00:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,helps one transcend\Nthe identification with the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.38,1:01:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It can bring about major\Ntransformations in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.38,1:01:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It can bring about\Na major positive leap in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.40,1:01:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you tell out of body\Nfrom a near death experience
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.40,1:01:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's a lot of lack of sophistication\Nnot only in the general public
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.57,1:01:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but even some spiritual teachings.\NOut of body is one thing
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.57,1:01:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,near death experience is another.\NOut of body doesn't necessarily
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.57,1:01:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,change your calibratable\Nlevel of consciousness at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.57,1:01:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.\NYou can go out of body, come back in body
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.57,1:01:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and boy that was really interesting.\NBut that's really not
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.57,1:01:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a major shift to consciousness.\NNear death experience
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.92,1:01:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is of a\Ntotally different dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.38,1:01:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,One is just\Nawestruck by the
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.46,1:01:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,immensity of the realization\Nof the nature of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.46,1:01:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nthat that which you're experiencing
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.80,1:02:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is not different than that which\Nwho you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.15,1:02:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a major transformation\Nnear death experiences.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.15,1:02:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So to tell the truth\Nyou can calibrate before and after
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.15,1:02:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience.\NOut of body usually you'll be about the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.15,1:02:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,However out of body\Nyou do become more sophisticated.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.32,1:02:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You also have an etheric body.\NOne thing that you're quite certain of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.32,1:02:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as you're floating in space\Nis that you have an etheric body
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.32,1:02:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because now you're it.\NOut of body is
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.98,1:02:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of course quite exhilarating.\NIt happened to me many years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.01,1:02:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in those days\Nand nothing was heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.01,1:02:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I've recounted it before.\NIn a serious illness
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.01,1:02:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly there I was\Nlooking down at the body
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.01,1:03:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in the bed\Nand the interesting thing was
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.09,1:03:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the sense of self\Nwent with the etheric body.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.46,1:03:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to know\Nfeel, think, hear
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.46,1:03:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,reason, everything.\NThe sense of I was up here
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.46,1:03:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was down there.\NSo it is an opportunity
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.01,1:03:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize\Nthat the sense of self
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.01,1:03:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual self\Nis an energy body and not a physical body.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.36,1:03:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time\NI don't think it had any
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.42,1:03:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,particularly transformative experience.\NWhen I told my psychoanalyst
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.61,1:03:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,about it\NI was in psychoanalysis at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.90,1:03:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I bless him, dear Dr. Oversee\NI said
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.90,1:03:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,God almighty there was this experience\Nwhat you had a toxic psychosis there
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.90,1:03:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,with a duplication of the body image\Nand a rejection of one aspect of it
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.90,1:03:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said\Nyou're right, you're right
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.90,1:04:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we were both atheists\Nhe didn't think much of
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.19,1:04:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,God and religion and at the time\NI didn't either so
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.19,1:04:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we didn't have any problem with it\Nit was a toxic
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.21,1:04:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,couple of irritated brain cells\Nthat's all we knew about in those days.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.26,1:04:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright we've got some interesting\Nleading questions into the subject
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.26,1:04:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,which we're going to go into anyway.\NIn my talking about women of course
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.21,1:04:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,just using Mother's Day\Nas a point of reference
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.28,1:04:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not differentiating\Nmen from women because
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.28,1:04:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity of course is equally\Npresent
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.53,1:04:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the form that it takes within the\Nperceptual world is different
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.53,1:04:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean a man is different from a woman\Nwithin the physical world
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.53,1:04:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and symbolically\Nthey represent
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.53,1:04:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,symbolically in the unconscious\Nthose of you who are
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.53,1:05:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar with the work\Nof Jung and all
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.53,1:05:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that the archetype of\Nthe feminine and the archetype of the male
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.53,1:05:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,are two different things and historically\Nthey've always been
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.53,1:05:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,even the planets are named with various\Ngenders and the gods and all
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.38,1:05:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that's really a different subject\Nit's a subject
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.26,1:05:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of study in itself\Nthe origin of how this arises
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.26,1:05:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,how it expresses itself\Nthe divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.42,1:05:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of all is the same of course\NI was just talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.42,1:05:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,its expression\Nas a woman
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.42,1:05:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and then using that\Nto denote the importance of
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.57,1:05:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,context, how woman was conceived of\Nin the 1800s
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.57,1:05:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,early 1900s now\Nis a shift of context
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.73,1:05:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but the reality of course\Nhas not been changed at all
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.73,1:06:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,some of these\Nare a little too complicated
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.73,1:06:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't answer them\Nthey're beyond me
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.73,1:06:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,all right\NI'll take my notes about them
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.38,1:06:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,here we have\Nwe forgot to put this up before
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.38,1:06:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just a point of reference\Nit's a very useful point of reference
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.38,1:06:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because I get many requests\Nfrom all kinds of groups
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.38,1:06:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,publishers, writers and all\Nto reproduce it
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.38,1:06:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and I always tell them yes\Nbecause it's useful
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.44,1:06:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as a teaching\Nteaching device
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.44,1:06:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Npeople say well
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.80,1:06:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,see people can't seem to get out of\Nthe ego's
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.80,1:06:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,view of things being better\Nthan others or ranking them
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.80,1:06:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is there\Nis 500 better than 400
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.98,1:06:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,no, 500 is a different\Ndifferent problem than 400
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.98,1:07:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to have any calibrated\Nnumber at all indicates a problem
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.46,1:07:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're at 500 your problem is\N600
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.53,1:07:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,things aren't better than others\Nthey're just different than others
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.65,1:07:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,people that are just entering the 400s\Nare trying to
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.30,1:07:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,own the capacity of reason\Nand logic and all
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.36,1:07:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is what we call\Nsophomoric is usually something
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.36,1:07:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody that's just entered the 400s\Nand they're dazzled by their capacity
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.36,1:07:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to use logic and thinking\Nand
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.48,1:07:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because they don't realize its downside\Nthey take it to the ridiculous extreme
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.48,1:07:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying\Nand then they write
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.09,1:07:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,legislation\NI mean it's okay
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.09,1:08:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the abstract but you should try to live\Nwith it
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.57,1:08:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I read somewhere that the\Nthe IRS regs run
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.57,1:08:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,58,000 pages and of course\Nyou know as a taxpayer
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.57,1:08:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you are legally liable\Nfor knowing all of its contents
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.57,1:08:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize that\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.57,1:08:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it's unknowable the government can't\Nunderstand it so it makes you responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.57,1:08:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,for knowing it\Nso I mean that's the intellect gone wild
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.06,1:08:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,without any limitation\Nso ranking would be then
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.06,1:08:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind's\Nproclivity for status
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.22,1:08:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and things like this and then projecting it onto\Nthese fields
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.25,1:08:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing is better than anything else\Nit's different than
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.34,1:08:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,something else because it's addressing\Na whole different problem
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.50,1:08:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it's addressing a whole different problem\Nis loss
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.35,1:08:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the occasion for grief\Nor is it
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.43,1:09:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the gateway to freedom and elation\Ndepends on who you lost eh
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.42,1:09:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah\Nso you see you don't have
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.64,1:09:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to mourn loss at all\Nyou can see that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.73,1:09:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,loss is the occasion\Nyou know let's say you own a whole head of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.31,1:09:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,cattle and they're all dead by morning\Nterrible disease
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.69,1:09:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,well you don't have to get up and milk them\NI'll tell you that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.97,1:09:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,four o'clock in the morning in the midwest\Nthrough the snow and the ice and pitch blackness
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.97,1:09:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,with snow up to here\Nand walk through all that cattle poo
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.07,1:09:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to milk this thing\Nalright
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.89,1:09:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so every loss then\Ncan be recontextualized
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.89,1:09:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,as an opportunity for freedom\Nas valuable as that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.89,1:10:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,position may have been\Nit still is the opportunity now
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.89,1:10:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to discover a new life\Nthe company collapses
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.38,1:10:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you lose your position\Nis that a loss
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.38,1:10:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it is only if you hang on to the past\Nwhat is really going on
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.34,1:10:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is you're afraid of the freedom\Nthat the dissolution of that commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.36,1:10:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,now opens up\Nyou're now free to become anything you want
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.36,1:10:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,go anywhere you want\Nare you going to stay in the same part of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.14,1:10:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,same part of the country\Nin other words it's sort of scary
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.26,1:10:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the freedom that you had\Nalright so
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.46,1:10:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,ranking then would be just a projection\Nthat we project onto this
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.46,1:10:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and the question often arises\Nhow do you see perfection
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.48,1:10:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in any and all conditions\Nbecause perception is a projection
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.64,1:10:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nyou will find what you're looking for
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.64,1:10:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the whole basis of\Nquantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.64,1:11:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason they stop calling things measurements\Nis because
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.25,1:11:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,what is found is\Nthe consequence of what you're looking for
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.07,1:11:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the observed is\Nthen seen as a function
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.81,1:11:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of the observer\Nthe observer
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.73,1:11:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the observer is what determines\Nwhat's observed
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.81,1:11:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,now what's observed\Nwhat's observed
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.61,1:11:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on intention\Nwe said that calibrated level
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.77,1:11:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness\Nas well as karma has to do with
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.77,1:11:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual intention\Nnow spiritual intention doesn't
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.26,1:11:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,fluctuate\Nit tends to move quite slowly
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.30,1:11:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,although you can have a major event\Nsuch as a near death experience
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.30,1:11:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or a spiritual intention\Nsuddenly takes a giant leap
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.68,1:11:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the moment to moment\Nlittle angriness, irritation, regrets
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.68,1:12:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,all these things\Nthose are not fluctuations on the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.68,1:12:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness is pretty steady\Nit's set up by the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.89,1:12:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic\Nkarmic development
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.89,1:12:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of\Nyour spiritual commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.07,1:12:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so the spiritual commitment then\Ntends to prevail
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.07,1:12:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,fluctuations may occur\Nonly in a fleeting thought
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.21,1:12:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you calibrated a thought\Nthe thoughts may jump all over
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.23,1:12:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but that which you are\Ndoesn't change that easily
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.23,1:12:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and people involved in spiritual work\Nknow
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.27,1:12:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,how difficult that is\Nto get it to change
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.27,1:12:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so\Nit's pretty much set
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.27,1:12:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and determined\Nhow you see the world
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.97,1:12:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrated level of energy\Nis influenced
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.97,1:12:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,then through your own decision\Nis it influenced by the group
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.06,1:13:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,yes\NI think so
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.13,1:13:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you calibrated a level of consciousness\Nis influenced by the group
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.13,1:13:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with which you identify\Nyeah
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.13,1:13:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it is influenced\Nbecause you are saying
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.13,1:13:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I see that as my reality\Nso it isn't so much the group
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.13,1:13:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you\Nare verifying that the group
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.35,1:13:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,represents your own\Nspiritual goal
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.42,1:13:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,not killing innocent children\Nmay be a very important
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.11,1:13:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual learning down here\Nthere are certain very large
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.11,1:13:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,religious groups in the world right now\Nwhere getting up this far
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.11,1:13:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is a great advance\Ngetting over 70
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.22,1:13:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is a major improvement\Nthat God is not pleased by your
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.65,1:13:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,killing thousands of innocent women and children\Nwould seem so
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.81,1:13:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,ludicrous to us\Nbut it might be a tremendous
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.81,1:14:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,aha to somebody\Nso as you move up
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.07,1:14:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,your own spiritual awareness moves up\Nthe group that you find useful at one time
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.07,1:14:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you are going to outgrow the group\Neventually you outgrow all groups
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.34,1:14:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so the group is useful\Nas mutual support
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.02,1:14:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Ncontinuous feedback
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.02,1:14:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,helps to clarify one's understanding\Nof that particular religious position
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.02,1:14:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or spiritual position\Nand then one moves on
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.31,1:14:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we spoke\Nthere were a number of different groups
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.73,1:14:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,people asked me about individually\NI don't like to do them publicly
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.93,1:14:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you see by their fruits you shall know them\Nwe don't have to ask what
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.55,1:14:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Nthe calibrated level of certain
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.22,1:14:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,groups and their actions\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.47,1:14:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,by their fruits you shall know them\Nso we did write something about
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.77,1:15:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference between a true spiritual\Ngroup and a cult
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.77,1:15:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,cults calibrate below 200\Nthat's the quickest way
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.77,1:15:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a cult is non-integrist\Nso a cult may take the name
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.77,1:15:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of a great leader or avatar\Nor spiritual guru or whatever
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.77,1:15:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and call itself that\Nand then underneath the guise of that
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.77,1:15:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,really become a political action\Ngroup
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.18,1:15:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the one in China that's having trouble\Nwith the government you see
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.47,1:15:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,its problem is\Nthat it didn't stick to just
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.47,1:15:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,strictly spiritual it got political\Nwhen it got political
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.47,1:15:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it began to challenge the Chinese authority\Nall governments
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.47,1:15:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,by nature protect themselves\Nthat's why they're your government
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.47,1:15:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,so China\Noutlawed them right
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.47,1:15:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Falun Gong I think is the name of it\Nso if you stay home and meditate
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.47,1:15:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and do good works the government will not take\Na position about you
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.47,1:15:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you start getting out there with the parade\Nand you're going to overthrow the
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.47,1:16:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,regime and put in your\Nphilosophical concepts
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.47,1:16:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,prepare to die\Nyou know prepare to die
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.56,1:16:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you can make a grandstand statement\Nbut that isn't what makes the world
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.56,1:16:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,turn you know what I'm saying\Nso a cult can take on the name of a great
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.06,1:16:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,leader call itself\Nyou know the holy church
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.06,1:16:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of God and\Nthe holy church of God
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.68,1:16:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the name of the holy church of God\Nburned down the homes
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.68,1:16:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of whatever\Nyou know what I'm saying
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.68,1:16:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,just because they call themselves that doesn't mean anything\Nalright so we define
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.68,1:16:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference between a cult and a truly\Nintegrative spiritual group
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.68,1:16:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of course we as a group know all you have to do\Nis calibrate them
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.68,1:16:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but to the world\Nthat which is of God
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.86,1:16:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,gives forth love and peace\Nit's as simple as that
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.86,1:17:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,love and peace is what radiates from it\Nsometimes that
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.77,1:17:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes the original of the spirit\Nthe originator or the original speaker
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.77,1:17:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of that spiritual truth\Nit is loving and pure
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.77,1:17:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but then that's grabbed by other groups\Nwho then run with it
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.77,1:17:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and use it as justification\Nto
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.89,1:17:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,convert people by the sword\NJesus meant the sword of truth right
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.02,1:17:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't mean\Nthe sword of steel
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.14,1:17:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's misused\Nthen for other ends
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.81,1:17:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,we notice\Nthat people are born
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.69,1:17:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,at different levels of consciousness\Nthe very instant of birth
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.69,1:17:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's another question having to do\Nwith geography I meant today
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.69,1:17:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a transparency\Nto project with the world map
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.69,1:18:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,showing calibrating the various\Nlevels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.82,1:18:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and prevailing civilizations\Nover the world
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.82,1:18:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's very interesting\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.27,1:18:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you see that like\Nlight
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.78,1:18:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to attract light\Nthat's sort of true
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.78,1:18:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you're born with a\Nlevel of consciousness of
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.07,1:18:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,50 let's say\Nyou're very likely to get
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.59,1:18:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,born into a body\Nthat happens to be part of a civilization
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.59,1:18:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,civilization\Nthat in general
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.59,1:18:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates around 50\Nin other words
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.68,1:18:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like nothing happens by accident\Nthat if light
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.81,1:18:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,light tends to go to light\Nat the very moment of birth
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.89,1:18:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,at the very moment\Nbefore birth even
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.89,1:19:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the calibrated level of consciousness\Nof the entity is already
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.89,1:19:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,identifiable\Nwe can actually calibrate it
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.39,1:19:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,what we just said is true\Nthat's a fact
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.86,1:19:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we've done it over and over\Nso what we think is
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.46,1:19:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,unspiritual\Nlet's say we look at the lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.57,1:19:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of somebody here\Nand we go cluck cluck cluck
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.57,1:19:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah but that person came in\Nhere for them to be
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.86,1:19:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,at 100 or 150 is a major\Nadvance
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.86,1:19:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you can look\Nback at previous lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.97,1:19:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and these\Nareas that you transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.26,1:19:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,become very\Nimportant
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.82,1:19:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you stand out of that\Nlifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.93,1:19:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the lifetime of surmounting\Nphysical death
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.25,1:20:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it's thrilling\Nyou commit harry carry
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.78,1:20:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and ecstasy\Nthe second you're out of body
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.21,1:20:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,ecstasy\Nsurmounted that for all time
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.56,1:20:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,never again\Nto be inhibited by the fear of physical death
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.19,1:20:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that makes a very ferocious warrior\Nwho's not afraid of death
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.55,1:20:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the fearless warrior\Nyou can walk into a hail of bullets
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.55,1:20:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't give a rap about it\Nyou're no longer susceptible to that
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.78,1:20:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,well now you've transcended that level\Nthere's no point to
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.21,1:20:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,i don't have to get myself killed over and over\Nto get the point
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.21,1:20:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you got a physical body\Nyou see the thing laying there
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.21,1:20:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the other spirit and you laugh at each other\Ngreat job joe great job
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.21,1:20:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we both did it\Nso there's really no point to do that again
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.21,1:20:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to commit harry carry 10 or 12 times\Nyou get the point of it
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.27,1:20:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not pleasant\Nso i'd only do it once
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.27,1:21:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,if i were you\Nit isn't that one thing is better than another
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.65,1:21:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you see\Nas you grasp the totality
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.64,1:21:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness\Nas it has evolved throughout time
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.64,1:21:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and the way it manifests\Non this planet
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.73,1:21:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,as the evolution of life on this planet\Nevolving into mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.73,1:21:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,evolving into modern man\Nyou begin to realize
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.57,1:21:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're dealing with\Nyou're dealing with
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.27,1:21:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,like a profound morass\Nout of which consciousness is only
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.27,1:21:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,just barely popping it's little head\Nit didn't cross 200
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.30,1:21:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,until the late 1980s\Nin other words
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.30,1:21:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like\Nmodern consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.46,1:21:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is just being born now\Nwe're probably part of the birth process
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.81,1:21:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of\Nhomo spiritus
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.53,1:22:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and so\Nhomo spiritus is
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.89,1:22:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a declaration made by\Nthis great wonderful being here
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.57,1:22:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,homo spiritus is correct\Nit is the emergence of homo spiritus
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.57,1:22:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,okay\Nin the book i
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.57,1:22:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,then i say\Nthere is now
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.67,1:22:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,emerging out of this morass\Nof negativity
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.67,1:22:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,ignorance\Nand finally the 400s
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.85,1:22:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego\Nthe appearance of love which is relatively recent in the human condition
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.85,1:22:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as a prevailing\Nenergy
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.14,1:22:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we have now the emergence\Nof the spiritually aware being
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.14,1:22:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,aware of himself\Nas a spiritual reality
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.34,1:22:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the emergence of homo\Nspiritus
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.01,1:22:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,all the branches off the evolutionary tree\Nsee
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.01,1:23:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not a linear thing\Nwhere this gets better and better and better and better
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.01,1:23:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in the evolutionary tree\Nevolution by the way happens on the level of
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.01,1:23:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness then it manifests within\Nthe physical domain
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.19,1:23:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but you see it's branches off the tree\Nthis tree this branch goes off here
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.19,1:23:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,this branch doesn't just get longer\Nand bigger and better
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.19,1:23:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,no it stops there\Nit's potentiality has been realized
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.42,1:23:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,when it hits the perfection of that which it is\Nand then you see
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.84,1:23:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,later another branch off the tree\Nand then another branch higher
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.89,1:23:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,off the tree\Nyou see the one branch doesn't
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.13,1:23:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,so the evolution of consciousness\Nas it's expressed in
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.13,1:23:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind is not\Nthe continuous evolution of one
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.13,1:23:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,trend at all\Nit's the emergence of a new trend
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.13,1:23:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,a new trend\Nthose of us here today represent really
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.81,1:24:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,a new branch off the evolutionary tree\Nwe are not an improvement
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.81,1:24:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,on Cro-Magnon man\Nwe're not an improvement
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.34,1:24:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we're not an improvement on homo erectus\Nhomo erectus went here
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.34,1:24:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and he got as far as homo erectus could go\Nend of homo erectus
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.34,1:24:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,each of us then represents\Nwe have
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.81,1:24:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,a branch off the tree\Nand there's a new branch off the tree
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.81,1:24:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,called homo spiritus\Nthat's a fact
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.89,1:24:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that's so\Nand the group here
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.64,1:24:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly represents\Nthat which is homo spiritus
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.64,1:24:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the awareness that we're more than\Na physicality
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.64,1:24:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the awareness that we're more than a mind\Nthe recognition of
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.72,1:24:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual potential within\Nto be discovered and nurtured
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.72,1:24:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for it to flourish and blossom\Ndid the enderthal man
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.98,1:25:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,worry about these things?\Nno
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.98,1:25:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,not suitable\NI think Cro-Magnon man
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.10,1:25:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,was about 70\Nthat has to do with physical survival as an animal
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.80,1:25:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,good enough to eat, to mate\Nto stay alive
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.14,1:25:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's the animal\Nso he had to first perfect
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.35,1:25:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the ability to maintain life\Nwithin animal form
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.35,1:25:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,within biped form\Nand then consciousness went on
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.35,1:25:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness got bored with that one\Ngot bored with him
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.48,1:25:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,said he's boring\Nand went on and developed this Cro-Magnon
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.48,1:25:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and then on through the ages\Nwhat we see now
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.96,1:25:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is where the evolution of consciousness\Nis at its present moment
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.96,1:25:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,this moment here\Nthe evolution of human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.43,1:26:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time\Nthroughout eons and eons
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.65,1:26:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of time\Nhas resulted
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.75,1:26:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,in us\Nwe're it
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.75,1:26:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we are it\Namen
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.77,1:26:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we are it\Nwe are it
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.77,1:26:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the advancing edge of consciousness\Nis really what is here today
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.77,1:26:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is it not?\Nwhat is the ultimate truth
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.89,1:26:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,how does one reach it\Nwhat are the tools that are useful for the task
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.89,1:26:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,or the advancing edge of spiritual consciousness is\Nis it
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.47,1:26:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is it possible\Nin the old religions
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.47,1:26:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,well religion is one thing\Nspiritual truth is another
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.32,1:26:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,hypothetically at least in the beginning\Nthey are one and the same
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.32,1:26:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but we see throughout history\Nhow spiritual truth then gets destroyed
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.32,1:27:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,for secular means\Nand the original truth is lost within
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.32,1:27:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the more spiritually\Nadvanced person utilizes
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.10,1:27:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,what they realize\Nspiritual truth from that religion
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.10,1:27:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and lets the shaft go\Nlets the shaft go
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.10,1:27:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you eat meat on Friday or not\Nis really irrelevant to God
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.34,1:27:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see if that's a fact\Nthat's a fact
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.59,1:27:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,ok\Nwhen I grew up you didn't eat meat on Friday
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.65,1:27:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was respectful\Nwell no it was a sin
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.65,1:27:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,it was worse than respectful\Nhigh episcopal it was like catholic
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.65,1:27:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway you didn't eat meat on Friday\Nit was really out of respect
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.88,1:27:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for the religion\Nand respect for the teaching
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.88,1:27:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it got you in or out of heaven\NI don't know
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.88,1:27:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but as a kid I suppose I would worry\Nif you ate meat on a Friday and died
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.88,1:27:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd think you were going to the other place\Nwe have permission to do some
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.88,1:28:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,public leaders resist\Nthat are in the middle east resist
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.03,1:28:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself have wondered about\Nthis particular individual
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.03,1:28:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we have permission to calibrate him in public\Nhe resists
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.03,1:28:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,he's on TV every night so I guess he's not too timid\Nthis gentleman
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.03,1:28:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates over 200 resist\Nwow over 220
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.42,1:28:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,230\N240 wow 260
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.64,1:28:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,250\NArafat 250
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.44,1:28:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see Arafat was\Nat 250
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.44,1:28:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,10 years ago resisted\Nno now Arafat is
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.44,1:28:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting because we see a lot of\Nwell known in fact currently popular
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.44,1:28:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,gurus that wrote\Nbooks years ago when they were in a high space
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.44,1:28:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,usually in the mid 500s\Nand their books calibrate in high 500s
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.44,1:28:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you calibrate what is the energy of this\Nentity today you'll often find
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.44,1:28:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,they're like 130 common\Nvery big name gurus in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.27,1:29:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody goes oh when you mention their name\Nyou calibrate them to like 140
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.27,1:29:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or something you know\Nit's because they went up
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.06,1:29:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and then were hit by\Nyou might say their opposite
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.06,1:29:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and succumbed to the opposite\Nthat's how the cult is born
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.57,1:29:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have a certain charisma\Nwhen people start to follow you
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.57,1:29:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you start to believe your own publicity\Nyou start getting power over others
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.57,1:29:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you start telling them what to do\Nyou develop a cult
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.57,1:29:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to swear an oath\Nyou gotta pay money
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.57,1:29:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,get a thing on your whatchamacallit\Nand
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.64,1:29:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,every time the name of the leader\Nyou bow
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.15,1:29:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,even Est\NGod bless Est
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.15,1:29:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it was Werner right\Nit was Werner everything
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.15,1:29:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,bigger than a movie theater\Non the screen
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.15,1:29:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it was all Werner\Non the other hand Est taught some
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.15,1:29:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,terrific things\Nwith Est you can take off weight very easy
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.35,1:30:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you know\Nlots of good things in it
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.35,1:30:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,alright\Nso then the cult we see
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.38,1:30:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody asked me about various things\NI said I don't want to calibrate them in public
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.89,1:30:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the leader becomes charismatic in a cult\Nit becomes all Baba so and so
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.02,1:30:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,master so and so\Nmaster Baba
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.50,1:30:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so it all becomes all master Baba\Nwith many oohs and ahhs
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.50,1:30:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's like a personality cult\Nthen there's a
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.85,1:30:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,a specialness to belonging\Nto the group
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.85,1:30:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a group form that gets a name\Nmaybe an initiation ceremony
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.10,1:30:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nnow the group becomes
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.59,1:30:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you're either with them or not with them\Nyou know
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.61,1:30:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you're one of us or not one of us\Nso it becomes very
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.77,1:30:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of seeing yourself\Nas part of the all
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.42,1:30:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the allness of life\Nyou now become partitioned as special
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.42,1:31:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,special\Nso you're a member that makes you special
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.55,1:31:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,then there's group lingo\Nwhich is only known to the members of the group
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.55,1:31:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,there's the specialness of the cult leader\Nthere is a negative
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.69,1:31:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,reaction if you leave\Nif you decide you're going to leave
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.69,1:31:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the holy\Nrosary of the round table
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.22,1:31:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever\Nhorrible things happen to you
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.22,1:31:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,snakes in your mailbox\Nhate mail
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.22,1:31:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so there's a negative reaction\Nif you try to leave
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.27,1:31:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so you like become a prisoner\Nso the brainwashing
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.27,1:31:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,what is really brainwashing\Nis then proceeded about this organization
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.27,1:31:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,about its specialness\Noften it considers itself exclusive
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.27,1:31:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,some go so far as to say\Nthat they're the only ones
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.63,1:31:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that are going to get into heaven\Nyou know it's a little hard to imagine
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.72,1:31:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,how many people are going to believe that\Nso there's a specialness
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.81,1:32:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,a uniqueness\Na cult-like atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.81,1:32:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,a specialness to belonging\Nor not belonging
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.81,1:32:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,various titles go with it\Nand after a while
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.17,1:32:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,there's probably a lot to be learned\Nthere's a lot to be learned
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.48,1:32:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,at that level\Nbut then at a certain level
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.48,1:32:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to realize\Nthis is not freeing and liberating
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.48,1:32:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this is confining\Nthis is totalitarian
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.48,1:32:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,at its greatest expression\Nit becomes totalitarian
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.48,1:32:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,at that point your intuition will tell you\Nit's time to move on
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.97,1:32:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it's very often hard to see\Nbecause
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.97,1:32:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the adulation\Nwith which certain people
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.97,1:32:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,are held by large groups\Nso mass hysteria
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.02,1:32:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the suggestion of madness of crowds\Ntakes over
Dialogue: 0,1:32:51.02,1:32:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you're in a group\Nand everybody's going
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.28,1:32:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the charisma of the leader then\Nbecomes magnetic
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.28,1:33:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the adulation of the group\Ntends to be infectious
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.28,1:33:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,so you've got to watch\Nthat you don't get brainwashed
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.31,1:33:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the only thing a teacher can do\Nis reflect truth
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.31,1:33:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't make them special, unique\Nanything at all
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.31,1:33:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,don't forget to a realized person\Ntheir condition is just nothing
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.31,1:33:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just the way it is\Nis a cat's condition to a cat special?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.31,1:33:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,no, it's just being a cat\Nso
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.69,1:33:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,a true teacher is just like a cat\NI mean it just is what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.69,1:33:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's nothing to say about that\Nit's just being what one is
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.69,1:33:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?\Nso there would hardly be any
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.93,1:33:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,adulation expected from being what you are\Nthe cat doesn't expect me to say
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.93,1:33:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,oh great cat\Nbecause you are a cat
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.93,1:33:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence within is so powerful\Nit is of itself
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.93,1:33:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it is of itself\Nit bypasses all personhood
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.93,1:34:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so there is no one to\Ngo ooh and ahh over
